org.mitre.provenance.user

Class PrivilegeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mitre.provenance.user.PrivilegeSet

  • public class PrivilegeSet
extends Object
    A conjunction of PrivilegeClass objects. Users can have privilege sets, or PLUS objects can require them for access.
    Author:
    dmallen, achapman

      • dominates

        public boolean dominates(PrivilegeClass c)
                  throws PLUSException
        Indicate whether this set of privileges dominates a particular class. If a member of this set dominates a particular class, then the user possessing that set is authorized to see data at that privilege class.
        Parameters:
        c - the class to check
        Returns:
        true if any privilege class in the set dominates c
        Throws:
        PLUSException

      • dominates

        public boolean dominates(PrivilegeSet other)
                  throws PLUSException
        Determine whether this privilege set dominates another.
        Parameters:
        other - the other you want to check.
        Returns:
        true if this privilege set contains a set of privilege classes that dominates all privilege classes in the other privilege set, false otherwise. In the case of incomparable PrivilegeSets, this method will return false.
        Throws:
        PLUSException
